97
00:09:28,490 --> 00:09:29,600
Hello?

98
00:09:33,130 --> 00:09:35,070
Hang up. I'm in the toilet.

99
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:38,340
That's nothing new. Why be shy all of a sudden?

100
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:39,510
We're family.

101
00:09:40,070 --> 00:09:42,410
What job is ever laid-back?

102
00:09:46,010 --> 00:09:48,650
Why are you yelling all of a sudden?

103
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:50,880
I didn't...

104
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,790
I didn't do anything.

105
00:09:58,190 --> 00:09:59,230
Hang up.

106
00:10:16,910 --> 00:10:18,610
Is something the matter, Sir?

107
00:10:20,180 --> 00:10:21,450
I called to tell her

108
00:10:21,450 --> 00:10:24,520
I'll be late because of a reunion.

109
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:26,750
But I didn't get to say that at all.

110
00:10:26,890 --> 00:10:27,890
Why?

111
00:10:27,950 --> 00:10:30,190
Was she already angry?

112
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:33,690
I can't talk to her nowadays.

113
00:10:35,230 --> 00:10:36,500
She's so...

114
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:38,240
high and mighty.

115
00:10:38,260 --> 00:10:39,700
Is she going through menopause?

116
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,200
Menopause?

117
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,300
You said she's older than you.

118
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:46,610
She's only 5 years older.

119
00:10:47,970 --> 00:10:49,580
It can't be.

120
00:10:52,410 --> 00:10:54,180
Could it really be menopause?

121
00:10:57,780 --> 00:11:00,650
It's not easy living with an older woman.

122
00:11:00,790 --> 00:11:03,390
Consider that when you get married.

123
00:11:03,390 --> 00:11:05,760
Why get married? I'm not going to.

124
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:07,030
Why?

125
00:11:07,230 --> 00:11:08,730
What's wrong with marriage?

126
00:11:10,230 --> 00:11:12,600
It's inconvenient. From beginning to end.

127
00:11:12,930 --> 00:11:14,370
Inconvenient...

128
00:11:15,370 --> 00:11:16,940
Right...

129
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:18,700
It's inconvenient.

130
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:22,070
Marriage is losing myself.

131
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,280
What?

132
00:11:27,450 --> 00:11:30,450
Why haven't I thought of that before?

133
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:34,350
Because you're earnest.

134
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,420
Am I earnest?

135
00:11:36,420 --> 00:11:37,590
Yes.

136
00:11:37,590 --> 00:11:38,860
Even your appearance is.

137
00:11:52,610 --> 00:11:54,040
If it's a reunion,

138
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:56,350
then you'll be out till 12 or 1 AM?

139
00:11:56,380 --> 00:11:58,780
About 1 or 2 AM.

140
00:11:58,980 --> 00:12:00,550
3 AM if I'm really late.

141
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:04,750
2 AM, 3 AM, 3 AM, 3 AM...

142
00:12:05,650 --> 00:12:07,990
It's a matter of texting or calling.

143
00:12:07,990 --> 00:12:09,860
Calling would be better, right?

144
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:12,690
But I'm scared to call her.

145
00:12:12,690 --> 00:12:16,030
Apologize for what happened via text.

146
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:18,300
Apologize? For what?

147
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:19,600
You know.

148
00:12:19,770 --> 00:12:22,540
"Come to think of it, I was insensitive."

149
00:12:22,540 --> 00:12:23,840
Something like that.

150
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:25,240
Oh, right, right.

151
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:27,740
"I have a reunion, so I'll be late today."

152
00:12:27,740 --> 00:12:29,640
- Oh.
- "I'll be home before 12 AM."

153
00:12:29,980 --> 00:12:33,550
Then around 12 AM, you say, "We're wrapping up."

154
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:34,980
Then at 1 AM,

155
00:12:35,210 --> 00:12:37,120
"I'm trying to get a cab."

156
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:40,490
"Since I'm in Gangnam, there's so much traffic..."

157
00:12:40,490 --> 00:12:41,890
If you go on like this,

158
00:12:41,890 --> 00:12:43,500
you'll hold out until 2:30 AM.

159
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:44,720
Wow.

160
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:47,190
It all sounds so smooth.

161
00:12:47,690 --> 00:12:49,460
What's important to women is

162
00:12:49,460 --> 00:12:52,360
emotional time, rather than physical time.

163
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:55,230
Wow.

164
00:12:55,470 --> 00:12:56,900
What are you?

165
00:12:57,300 --> 00:12:58,300
Are you a woman?

166
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,030
Oh, my.

167
00:12:59,410 --> 00:13:00,610
You didn't know?

168
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:01,740
Hmph.

169
00:13:03,010 --> 00:13:04,280
I'll be off now, Sir.

170
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:05,750
Okay. Bye.

171
00:13:14,220 --> 00:13:16,520
Jin Jeong-su
Come to think of it, I was insensitive.

172
00:13:17,920 --> 00:13:21,130
Jin Jeong-su
I'll be late due to a college reunion.

173
00:13:23,430 --> 00:13:25,830
Jin Jeong-su
I'll be home by midnight.

174
00:13:42,980 --> 00:13:44,250
You know...

175
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:46,490
Normally, I'd just give that to you.

176
00:13:46,820 --> 00:13:47,820
What?

177
00:13:48,220 --> 00:13:51,160
Don't throw it away. Wash it and use it again.

178
00:15:06,770 --> 00:15:07,700
So...

179
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:11,800
Would you feel better

180
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:14,470
if I get off on the next stop?

181
00:15:22,050 --> 00:15:25,480
This situation isn't easy for me either.

182
00:15:28,650 --> 00:15:30,820
But I can't

183
00:15:31,060 --> 00:15:32,830
