202
00:17:16,830 --> 00:17:18,900
It's not like the past...

203
00:17:20,330 --> 00:17:21,730
Like the 90s.

204
00:17:21,930 --> 00:17:24,830
Exchanging numbers isn't a big deal nowadays.

205
00:17:25,970 --> 00:17:27,210
What messenger do you use?

206
00:17:30,610 --> 00:17:31,610
Text?

207
00:17:34,210 --> 00:17:35,210
Or...

208
00:17:35,450 --> 00:17:36,580
KakaoTalk?

209
00:17:41,250 --> 00:17:42,660
Okay, KakaoTalk.

210
00:17:45,790 --> 00:17:47,310
What did that mean?

211
00:17:47,590 --> 00:17:48,590
What?

212
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:50,530
You scrutinized me,

213
00:17:50,530 --> 00:17:53,400
then asked if I used KakaoTalk.

214
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:57,470
I didn't scrutinize you.

215
00:17:57,740 --> 00:17:59,100
I glanced at you.

216
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:01,740
You can tell by my clothes?

217
00:18:04,810 --> 00:18:07,650
Clothes have nothing to do with KakaoTalk.

218
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:11,880
In the past and even now,

219
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:14,950
people use KakaoTalk a lot.

220
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:16,720
I was just asking.

221
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:18,690
You're very sensitive.

222
00:18:18,820 --> 00:18:20,160
What do you use?

223
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:21,460
I use everything.

224
00:18:21,660 --> 00:18:24,430
Text, KakaoTalk, more recent DMs.

225
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:27,000
What fits the age and situation.

226
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:29,030
It's a diverse world.

227
00:18:32,270 --> 00:18:35,170
I'll pay for the handkerchief now.

228
00:18:35,170 --> 00:18:36,170
Jeez.

229
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:38,710
You're being too cold.

230
00:18:38,710 --> 00:18:40,350
I already gave it to you.

231
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:43,080
You're right. I use KakaoTalk.

232
00:18:43,820 --> 00:18:45,750
Do you have change?

233
00:18:54,090 --> 00:18:55,730
You want me to give you change?

234
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:58,560
I only have a KRW 50,000 bill.

235
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:03,100
Well...

236
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:04,600
This is...

237
00:19:05,270 --> 00:19:06,770
US $350...

238
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:09,940
The exchange rate is KRW 1,200 for a dollar.

239
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:11,170
I think

240
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:14,080
I'll have to take it all.

241
00:19:22,820 --> 00:19:24,720
It might be because of the day.

242
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:28,460
Or it might be because you're sadder than me.

243
00:19:29,330 --> 00:19:30,600
My heart

244
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,430
is leaping

245
00:19:33,270 --> 00:19:34,730
and jolting.

246
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,140
I wanted to be kind.

247
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:48,230
That is my good will.

248
00:19:48,980 --> 00:19:50,820
This is your good will.

249
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:53,360
Let's leave it at that.

250
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:55,280
You should've done that beforehand.

251
00:20:55,280 --> 00:20:57,350
We're on a bus, for crying out loud.

252
00:20:58,150 --> 00:20:59,990
At this rate, you'll never get a job.

253
00:20:59,990 --> 00:21:01,890
I can't do the attendance check beforehand.

254
00:21:02,860 --> 00:21:04,590
I'll turn it off after the roll call.

255
00:21:04,590 --> 00:21:07,430
I have to answer the roll call to get back my money.

256
00:21:08,530 --> 00:21:10,460
You're paid to answer the roll call?

257
00:21:10,460 --> 00:21:12,100
No, it's not that.

258
00:21:12,630 --> 00:21:14,630
It's a long story to explain.

259
00:21:16,870 --> 00:21:18,200
How much do you have?

260
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:25,440
I'm taking KRW 20,000.

261
00:21:27,150 --> 00:21:28,150
Oh.

262
00:21:29,410 --> 00:21:31,280
What was that money earlier?

263
00:21:33,020 --> 00:21:33,720
Huh?

264
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:35,750
You just put it in Jeong-woo's pocket.

265
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:37,020
The folded bill.

266
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:38,720
Looked like there was a story behind it.

267
00:21:40,230 --> 00:21:42,530
You seem infinitely dense,

268
00:21:42,530 --> 00:21:44,000
but you're infinitely sensitive.

269
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:46,470
A client folded it? Like a talisman?

270
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:47,700
Oh.

271
00:21:47,700 --> 00:21:50,440
So other women won't cling to you?

272
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:53,170
Yeah, could be.

273
00:21:54,140 --> 00:21:56,540
What? There really is a story?

274
00:21:57,640 --> 00:22:00,450
I'm putting an address in your wallet.

275
00:22:01,850 --> 00:22:02,980
What address?

276
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:07,090
Jeong-woo's sister's address I got from the police.

277
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:09,890
- Sister?
- Yes.

278
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:11,060
Why?

279
00:22:11,060 --> 00:22:12,420
What do you mean?

280
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:20,230
What's this?

281
00:22:20,230 --> 00:22:22,270
When we were scattering his ashes in the park,

282
00:22:22,270 --> 00:22:23,870
I grabbed a spoonful.

283
00:22:23,870 --> 00:22:25,370
- Of what?
- Jeong-woo.

284
00:22:25,370 --> 00:22:26,570
What about him?

