849
00:55:24,750 --> 00:55:26,180
Then

850
00:55:26,180 --> 00:55:29,050
you should've married her no matter what.

851
00:55:29,990 --> 00:55:32,490
You two were madly in love, but married separately.

852
00:55:32,490 --> 00:55:33,520
Making us all uncomfortable.

853
00:55:33,520 --> 00:55:36,460
You didn't marry your first love either.

854
00:55:36,890 --> 00:55:39,160
My situation is different.

855
00:55:40,060 --> 00:55:42,630
Gyeong-eun said she's okay with you being here.

856
00:55:42,630 --> 00:55:44,370
That's not why I'm uncomfortable.

857
00:55:49,270 --> 00:55:52,140
Didn't she say her husband was sick?

858
00:55:52,140 --> 00:55:53,240
Yeah.

859
00:55:53,240 --> 00:55:54,610
Cancer.

860
00:55:55,010 --> 00:55:58,010
But last time, she said he got well after surgery.

861
00:56:00,620 --> 00:56:01,750
Gyeong-eun

862
00:56:02,220 --> 00:56:04,420
talked about you a lot when we met.

863
00:56:05,460 --> 00:56:06,520
About me?

864
00:56:06,520 --> 00:56:08,860
- Yeah.
- Don't look excited.

865
00:56:08,860 --> 00:56:10,190
She's living a good life.

866
00:56:10,190 --> 00:56:11,290
Don't even think about it.

867
00:56:11,290 --> 00:56:12,970
Are you drunk already?

868
00:56:13,300 --> 00:56:15,230
Watch what you're saying.

869
00:56:15,900 --> 00:56:17,530
You don't know anything.

870
00:56:18,070 --> 00:56:20,040
You picking a fight?

871
00:56:20,040 --> 00:56:21,600
Where are you going?

872
00:56:21,600 --> 00:56:23,240
You're not going home, are you?

873
00:56:23,240 --> 00:56:24,640
Hey, eat up.

874
00:56:24,640 --> 00:56:26,580
The meat is all cooked.

875
00:56:27,160 --> 00:56:28,580
This is delicious.

876
00:56:52,340 --> 00:56:54,540
- Gyeong-eun!
- Hey!

877
00:56:54,540 --> 00:56:55,440
- Oh, hi!
- Hi!

878
00:56:55,440 --> 00:56:57,240
- It's been such a long time!
- Hi!

879
00:57:00,480 --> 00:57:02,350
You look so pretty!

880
00:57:02,350 --> 00:57:03,950
Long time no see!

881
00:57:13,760 --> 00:57:14,590
Gyeon-eun, have a drink.

882
00:57:14,590 --> 00:57:17,260
- Let's have a drink.
- Pour me a glass.

883
00:57:17,260 --> 00:57:19,760
It's so good to see you.

884
00:57:19,760 --> 00:57:21,000
How have you been?

885
00:57:22,170 --> 00:57:24,030
Cheers!

886
00:57:24,030 --> 00:57:26,500
Good to see you!

887
00:57:31,370 --> 00:57:32,740
Eat up, Gyeong-eun.

888
00:57:32,740 --> 00:57:34,840
Okay. Let's eat.

889
00:57:35,780 --> 00:57:37,050
- You came straight from the office?
- Yeah.

890
00:57:37,050 --> 00:57:39,280
You haven't changed a bit.

891
00:57:39,280 --> 00:57:40,750
You've gotten prettier.

892
00:57:40,750 --> 00:57:42,410
You look so good.

893
00:57:43,590 --> 00:57:45,990
Five-way Intersection Pharmacy

894
00:57:55,670 --> 00:57:56,670
Huh?

895
00:57:56,970 --> 00:57:58,170
You're closing up?

896
00:57:58,170 --> 00:57:59,370
Long time no see.

897
00:57:59,370 --> 00:58:00,400
What brings you here?

898
00:58:03,170 --> 00:58:04,610
Did you not get my monthly rent?

899
00:58:04,610 --> 00:58:06,710
I got it.

900
00:58:06,710 --> 00:58:07,710
Then why...

901
00:58:08,450 --> 00:58:09,910
Oh, are you not feeling well?

902
00:58:09,910 --> 00:58:11,820
Give me that thing.

903
00:58:13,280 --> 00:58:14,280
That thing?

904
00:58:14,680 --> 00:58:16,720
That thing I drank the other time.

905
00:58:18,050 --> 00:58:19,120
Oh, that!

906
00:58:19,120 --> 00:58:20,690
Yeah, that.

907
00:58:20,690 --> 00:58:22,160
You want to drink it now?

908
00:58:22,260 --> 00:58:24,460
It's not good to drink it before going to bed.

909
00:58:24,460 --> 00:58:25,700
Are you going somewhere?

910
00:58:26,260 --> 00:58:28,470
My insides feel clogged up and I'm suffocating.

911
00:58:28,470 --> 00:58:29,830
Where would I go?

912
00:58:30,270 --> 00:58:32,070
Oh, you want digestive medicine.

913
00:58:32,070 --> 00:58:34,500
I thought you were looking for an invigorating drink.

914
00:58:34,500 --> 00:58:36,540
So I thought you were going somewhere nice.

915
00:58:36,540 --> 00:58:38,040
Somewhere nice for an old person?

916
00:58:38,040 --> 00:58:39,040
You mean heaven?

917
00:58:39,040 --> 00:58:40,680
Oh, stop that.

918
00:58:40,680 --> 00:58:42,660
You're still young.

919
00:58:46,350 --> 00:58:47,920
Drink it slowly.

920
00:58:50,950 --> 00:58:53,260
Ah, that's more like it.

921
00:58:53,590 --> 00:58:56,330
What did you eat that caused you indigestion?

922
00:58:56,330 --> 00:58:57,660
Did you have too much for dinner?

923
00:58:57,660 --> 00:58:59,340
I haven't eaten anything.

924
00:58:59,660 --> 00:59:02,730
But I've been stressed for a few days.

925
00:59:03,630 --> 00:59:04,900
Right.

926
00:59:05,240 --> 00:59:07,340
Stress is the worst.

927
00:59:07,640 --> 00:59:09,640
Did something unsettling happen?

928
00:59:11,540 --> 00:59:14,380
You're kind, smart,

929
00:59:14,380 --> 00:59:15,750
prettier the more I look

930
00:59:16,180 --> 00:59:17,810
and you speak so prettily.

931
00:59:18,950 --> 00:59:20,250
Me?

932
00:59:20,650 --> 00:59:23,650
If my brother heard you, he'd barf.

933
00:59:23,650 --> 00:59:25,390
You're funny and easygoing.

934
00:59:25,960 --> 00:59:28,020
Oh, stop it now.

935
00:59:28,020 --> 00:59:29,830
I'm going to have indigestion.

936
00:59:29,830 --> 00:59:34,160
You should've met my son when I asked you to.

937
00:59:34,560 --> 00:59:35,730
Not that again.

938
00:59:35,730 --> 00:59:37,430
It's been more than 10 years.

939
00:59:38,370 --> 00:59:39,970
It's already been that long?

940
00:59:39,970 --> 00:59:40,970
Yes.

941
00:59:41,300 --> 00:59:43,210
And your son is already married.

942
00:59:44,940 --> 00:59:47,440
That's right.

943
00:59:47,780 --> 00:59:50,480
No matter how upset I am, I shouldn't say this.

944
00:59:50,780 --> 00:59:52,720
I'll be punished.

945
00:59:53,450 --> 00:59:54,420
Thank you

946
00:59:54,420 --> 00:59:58,320
for locking up my mouth before I sinned again.

947
01:00:00,160 --> 01:00:01,620
Want me to get more digestive medicine?

948
01:00:01,620 --> 01:00:02,990
The syrup kind and pills?

949
01:00:05,100 --> 01:00:07,130
You're so kind and thoughtful.

950
01:00:07,960 --> 01:00:10,500
Oh, no, I'm not.

951
01:00:10,500 --> 01:00:12,240
I'm only good-natured in the pharmacy.

952
01:00:12,240 --> 01:00:14,040
At home, I'm like a fighting bull.

953
01:00:14,470 --> 01:00:17,770
That's better than the crazy cow at home.

954
01:00:17,770 --> 01:00:18,770
What?

955
01:00:18,880 --> 01:00:20,910
I was talking to myself.

956
01:00:24,880 --> 01:00:27,550
You're making me blush.

957
01:00:30,390 --> 01:00:31,690
Dad!

958
01:00:33,020 --> 01:00:35,130
Open up.

959
01:00:36,960 --> 01:00:39,200
Should I call the ambulance? Huh?

960
01:00:40,660 --> 01:00:42,500
Seriously...

961
01:00:55,650 --> 01:00:57,090
Are you okay, Dad?

962
01:00:58,410 --> 01:00:59,480
Wait.

963
01:01:00,620 --> 01:01:02,720
Did you get an upset stomach after eating this?

964
01:01:02,720 --> 01:01:03,890
No.

965
01:01:05,960 --> 01:01:08,060
Where did you get this?

966
01:01:08,390 --> 01:01:09,390
Did someone give it to you?

967
01:01:09,390 --> 01:01:10,660
No.

968
01:01:12,000 --> 01:01:14,360
I got a doggy bag for the leftovers at lunch.

969
01:01:26,510 --> 01:01:27,640
You...

970
01:01:29,250 --> 01:01:31,280
went there for lunch?

971
01:01:32,820 --> 01:01:33,850
Huh?

972
01:01:34,750 --> 01:01:36,520
Who did you meet for lunch?

973
01:01:37,320 --> 01:01:39,520
I didn't meet anyone.

974
01:01:39,620 --> 01:01:42,290
Who'd you meet? Jeong-su?

975
01:01:42,630 --> 01:01:44,330
No.

976
01:01:44,890 --> 01:01:48,370
I'm fine. Go home and fix dinner.

977
01:01:48,370 --> 01:01:51,030
Jeong-su said he'll be late. He has a reunion.

978
01:01:51,030 --> 01:01:52,840
Still, go home.

979
01:01:52,840 --> 01:01:56,070
How can I leave when you're sick like this?

980
01:01:57,610 --> 01:01:58,680
Dad.

981
01:01:59,110 --> 01:02:01,610
If it's bad, let's go to the hospital.

982
01:02:01,610 --> 01:02:03,150
No.

983
01:02:03,410 --> 01:02:04,880
I'm not sick.

984
01:02:05,320 --> 01:02:07,180
It's not that kind of thing.

985
01:02:07,580 --> 01:02:09,420
Then what is it?

986
01:02:09,420 --> 01:02:13,490
What made you look so miserable in one day?

987
01:02:14,020 --> 01:02:16,890
When you're old, you always look miserable.

988
01:02:22,830 --> 01:02:24,570
You met someone, right?

989
01:02:26,740 --> 01:02:27,740
Huh?

990
01:02:29,110 --> 01:02:31,040
Dad!

991
01:02:35,950 --> 01:02:36,950
Oh, dear.

992
01:02:37,950 --> 01:02:39,630
What is it, Dad? Huh?

993
01:02:40,620 --> 01:02:41,750
Tell me.

994
01:02:49,860 --> 01:02:50,890
I...

995
01:02:50,890 --> 01:02:51,890
Yeah.

996
01:02:53,360 --> 01:02:56,200
I thought hard all day.

997
01:02:58,330 --> 01:03:01,370
But I know no one in the police.

998
01:03:03,310 --> 01:03:06,640
I remembered someone from the Seosan family

999
01:03:06,640 --> 01:03:09,410
worked at a local police station,

1000
01:03:09,950 --> 01:03:12,280
so I called everyone I knew.

1001
01:03:13,950 --> 01:03:16,120
But they're all dead and gone.

1002
01:03:21,520 --> 01:03:22,690
I...

1003
01:03:25,130 --> 01:03:26,930
I lived a poor life

1004
01:03:27,900 --> 01:03:29,900
and you're suffering for that.

1005
01:03:33,400 --> 01:03:35,370
Since the police summoned you,

1006
01:03:35,370 --> 01:03:37,570
you must've been so scared alone.

1007
01:03:38,610 --> 01:03:40,740
I didn't know that.

1008
01:03:40,980 --> 01:03:42,950
I thought you were acting strange.

1009
01:03:43,610 --> 01:03:46,850
But I thought it was just family matters.

1010
01:03:47,550 --> 01:03:51,250
I thought it was about the miscarriage.

1011
01:03:55,320 --> 01:03:57,060
I'm such a fool

1012
01:03:58,160 --> 01:03:59,730
that I don't know even when I see it.

1013
01:04:01,230 --> 01:04:02,670
I'm a knucklehead.

1014
01:04:06,400 --> 01:04:07,870
You poor little thing.

1015
01:04:09,640 --> 01:04:11,810
You must've suffered so much.

1016
01:04:12,480 --> 01:04:13,780
I'm not little.

1017
01:04:16,850 --> 01:04:18,720
Did you meet Jeong-su for lunch?

1018
01:04:19,720 --> 01:04:21,420
Did he tell you?

1019
01:04:22,150 --> 01:04:24,450
No. I said it wasn't Jeong-su.

1020
01:04:24,450 --> 01:04:27,220
But there's no one else but Jeong-su.

1021
01:04:28,120 --> 01:04:30,660
It's not important who I met.

1022
01:04:31,930 --> 01:04:33,900
I should know.

1023
01:04:35,330 --> 01:04:37,770
Even if I can't do anything, I should know.

1024
01:04:43,370 --> 01:04:44,370
Was...

1025
01:04:45,510 --> 01:04:47,640
there a big misunderstanding?

1026
01:04:48,910 --> 01:04:51,910
The only bad words you know are stupid and jerk.

1027
01:04:51,910 --> 01:04:54,250
So what could you have said to go to the police?

1028
01:04:57,090 --> 01:04:58,920
There was a misunderstanding, right?

1029
01:05:00,620 --> 01:05:01,720
Right.

1030
01:05:02,760 --> 01:05:04,330
What you said is right.

1031
01:05:04,330 --> 01:05:05,700
There was a misunderstanding.

1032
01:05:07,100 --> 01:05:10,170
When do you go to the police station?

1033
01:05:10,170 --> 01:05:11,200
I'm coming with you.

1034
01:05:11,200 --> 01:05:14,140
That's nonsense. I'm old enough to go alone.

1035
01:05:14,140 --> 01:05:17,040
What does age have to do with it?

1036
01:05:17,040 --> 01:05:19,310
Even when you're 60, you're still my child.

1037
01:05:20,140 --> 01:05:21,840
They said I don't have to go.

1038
01:05:23,410 --> 01:05:24,780
I don't have to go.

1039
01:05:25,180 --> 01:05:26,050
Huh?

1040
01:05:26,580 --> 01:05:28,020
Really?

1041
01:05:28,020 --> 01:05:30,990
It's all been taken care of.

1042
01:05:30,990 --> 01:05:33,490
Like you said, there was a misunderstanding.

1043
01:05:34,920 --> 01:05:36,930
A long time ago...

1044
01:05:38,360 --> 01:05:39,600
There was someone

1045
01:05:39,600 --> 01:05:42,570
I got to know while making a book.

1046
01:05:43,870 --> 01:05:47,240
I guess she held a grudge against me.

1047
01:05:47,700 --> 01:05:49,910
So we met up and got things sorted.

1048
01:05:50,440 --> 01:05:52,380
I don't have to go to the police station.

1049
01:05:52,780 --> 01:05:54,180
Really?

1050
01:05:54,310 --> 01:05:55,310
Yes.

1051
01:05:56,580 --> 01:05:57,610
Are you sure?

1052
01:05:57,610 --> 01:05:59,050
Yes.

1053
01:06:14,930 --> 01:06:16,370
You think I'm crazy?

1054
01:06:16,630 --> 01:06:17,400
It wasn't me.

1055
01:06:17,400 --> 01:06:19,800
Then who was it? Only you and I know about it.

1056
01:06:20,470 --> 01:06:23,170
I'm telling you, it wasn't me.

1057
01:06:23,170 --> 01:06:24,370
Then was it your mother?

1058
01:06:24,370 --> 01:06:25,910
How can you...

1059
01:06:28,810 --> 01:06:30,580
I'm going to spend the night at my dad's house.

1060
01:06:30,580 --> 01:06:31,880
Don't wait up.

1061
01:06:31,880 --> 01:06:34,150
Do what you want,

1062
01:06:34,920 --> 01:06:36,190
but know that it wasn't me.

1063
01:06:37,150 --> 01:06:39,090
Let's talk tomorrow. I'm hanging up now.

1064
01:06:43,990 --> 01:06:45,730
That sounded pretty serious.

1065
01:06:46,660 --> 01:06:47,930
Was that your wife?

1066
01:06:48,430 --> 01:06:51,100
It's nothing. Nothing serious.

1067
01:06:52,400 --> 01:06:54,670
I came out to call home, too.

1068
01:06:59,410 --> 01:07:00,980
How's your wife?

1069
01:07:04,080 --> 01:07:06,020
You want to know how she is?

1070
01:07:09,520 --> 01:07:10,520
Hmph...

1071
01:07:10,920 --> 01:07:12,360
Can't I even ask?

1072
01:07:13,360 --> 01:07:14,920
Why are you so serious?

1073
01:07:22,270 --> 01:07:24,670
They're getting ready to hit another place.

1074
01:07:25,000 --> 01:07:26,570
Let's go inside.

1075
01:07:28,040 --> 01:07:29,870
You shouldn't have come.

1076
01:07:32,310 --> 01:07:35,140
If I knew you were coming, I wouldn't have come.

1077
01:07:36,850 --> 01:07:37,950
I just

1078
01:07:40,419 --> 01:07:42,690
wanted to see you one more time.

1079
01:07:43,850 --> 01:07:45,020
I wondered

1080
01:07:46,120 --> 01:07:48,289
how you were after that time.

1081
01:07:49,789 --> 01:07:51,789
Why would you wonder about that?

1082
01:07:55,999 --> 01:07:57,070
Just...

1083
01:08:01,100 --> 01:08:03,039
I still think about you first

1084
01:08:04,070 --> 01:08:06,080
whenever things get tough for me.

1085
01:08:08,680 --> 01:08:10,110
You're really

1086
01:08:11,749 --> 01:08:12,980
sickening.

1087
01:08:13,780 --> 01:08:14,780
Why?

1088
01:08:15,620 --> 01:08:17,289
Because I'm more honest than you?

1089
01:08:19,390 --> 01:08:20,860
You're honest?

1090
01:08:21,490 --> 01:08:23,629
I'm more honest than you.

1091
01:08:37,940 --> 01:08:39,440
My husband...

1092
01:08:46,850 --> 01:08:48,379
...is dying.

1093
01:08:52,860 --> 01:08:54,560
Since that time,

1094
01:08:55,589 --> 01:08:57,270
a year has passed, I think.

1095
01:08:59,230 --> 01:09:01,959
He's been in a nursing hospital all year.

1096
01:09:06,200 --> 01:09:08,740
I did my best.

1097
01:09:16,710 --> 01:09:18,950
But I got punished in the end.

1098
01:09:35,770 --> 01:09:36,770
Thank you.

1099
01:09:40,940 --> 01:09:45,940
Jeong A-ran
Can we talk over the phone?

1100
01:10:02,930 --> 01:10:04,760
Jeong-woo...

1101
01:10:06,100 --> 01:10:07,300
KRW 40 mil...

1102
01:10:08,060 --> 01:10:09,400
I'm selling clothes I don't wear

1103
01:10:09,400 --> 01:10:11,430
and a bunch of other stuff.

1104
01:10:11,430 --> 01:10:13,140
And this studio apartment

1105
01:10:13,140 --> 01:10:13,870
gets leased out quickly

1106
01:10:13,870 --> 01:10:16,940
so I'm thinking of putting it on the market.

1107
01:10:16,940 --> 01:10:18,410
You know the security deposit

1108
01:10:18,410 --> 01:10:20,040
for this place is KRW 15 mil.

1109
01:10:21,380 --> 01:10:23,280
I'll use KRW 5 mil. to move.

1110
01:10:25,250 --> 01:10:27,180
How long will you hold out?

1111
01:10:27,720 --> 01:10:29,390
Until you win the lottery?

1112
01:10:29,620 --> 01:10:30,850
Until you get a job.

1113
01:10:30,850 --> 01:10:32,090
When you get a job,

1114
01:10:32,090 --> 01:10:33,290
I'll clean up everything.

1115
01:10:33,290 --> 01:10:34,820
Winning the lottery will be faster.

1116
01:10:36,290 --> 01:10:37,560
She's still here.

1117
01:10:37,560 --> 01:10:38,290
Who?

1118
01:10:38,290 --> 01:10:39,400
Enjoy.

1119
01:10:39,860 --> 01:10:41,000
Min-jeong.

1120
01:10:41,160 --> 01:10:42,730
You watch your back with her.

1121
01:10:42,730 --> 01:10:44,430
She's the female version of me.

1122
01:10:44,430 --> 01:10:45,470
Oh.

1123
01:10:47,740 --> 01:10:48,800
I'm doomed.

1124
01:10:49,200 --> 01:10:51,640
It's the end of the world. The apocalypse.

1125
01:10:52,270 --> 01:10:53,270
Jeez.

1126
01:10:53,680 --> 01:10:54,960
How can this be?

1127
01:10:57,870 --> 01:10:59,310
